pullRequest.body:
Add the notion of Baire measurability for sets in a topological space, analogous to null measurability for sets in a measure space. 

A follow-up PR will add the Kuratowski-Ulam theorem.

theorem MeasurableSet.residualEq_isOpen [MeasurableSpace α] [BorelSpace α] (h : MeasurableSet s) :
```
This belongs in `Topology/Maps`.
This is called `Filter.Tendsto f (residual α) (residual β)`.
This belongs in the file where we prove other basic properties of `residual` (if `Homeomorph` is available there).

Currently this is Topology/GDelta, which is strange. What do you think of adding in this PR another new file, say Topology/Baire/Basic, where the definitions and basic properties of `residual` and `isMeager` go
(Oh and `Homeomorph is in fact not available there)
Does `Baire/Lemmas` have the required imports?
No. The only import of that file is `Topology/GDelta`
As @sgouezel told me a few years ago, using `variable`s for explicit arguments is not a good style. It's not hard to copy+paste them.
Is it the same as the recently added `coborder`?
Looks like it.
You don't need continuity here, see #15552

First, we define the notation `=ᵇ`. This denotes eventual equality with respect to the filter of
```
Can you scope these notations to the `Topology` namespace?

I don't think this type synonym is a good idea: if you want to make it usable properly, you should introduce a bunch of boilerplate (equivs between the initial type and its synonym, register the topological space structure on the type synonym, and so on). More importantly, you don't really use it below. I would just change the definition of `BaireMeasurableSet` to
```
open scoped MeasureTheory in
/-- We say a set is a `BaireMeasurableSet` if it differs from some Borel set by
a meager set. This forms a σ-algebra.

It is equivalent, and a more standard definition, to say that the set differs from
some *open* set by a meager set. See `BaireMeasurableSet.residual_eq_open` -/
def BaireMeasurableSet (s : Set α) : Prop := 
  MeasurableSet[EventuallyMeasurableSpace (α := α) (borel _) (residual _)] s
```
Ok, sure. I was just copying what was done for `NullMeasurable`. Do you know why the type synonym is used there?

```suggestion
    rw [coborder_eq_union_closure_compl] at this
```
Spaces after `rw`, here and elsewhere.
Could you prove that this is an equivalence ?
Could you move them if this is possible, or remove the comment that they should be moved?
